corresponding to those observed among distinct {\textless}i{\textgreater}Orconectes{\textless}i/{\textgreater} species. Genetic variation in the American range of these crayfish should therefore be further studied. Our study shows that DNA barcoding is useful for the rapid and accurate identification of exotic crayfish in Europe, and also provides insights into overall variation within these taxa.},
